Police are investigating a case of attempted murder after a man was shot in the chest outside a shop in Timothy Valley yesterday morning. Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said the incident took place just after 9am, when a taxi drove down Lingelihle Street and one of the occupants fired shots, hitting the unidentified man in the chest. She said two people were in the taxi. A case of attempted murder is being investigated. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share